question.q_19: If I have 0 points from lab excercises, can I pass with a grade of 5?

answers.answer: No, you cannot pass with a grade of 5 if you have 0 points from lab exercises. You need at least 14 points on the final exam to pass based on continuous assessment.

question.q_20: What are my options for consultations?

answers.answer: Your options for consultations include requesting a consultation with your teacher through MS Teams, browsing content on the Internet for additional explanations and examples, and viewing your own tickets in the My tickets menu option to see open and resolved questions.
Your options for consultations are to use the MS Teams platform, at times agreed with the teacher.
Consultations will take place through the MS Teams platform, at times agreed with the teacher.

Your options for consultations are to request a consultation with your teacher through MS Teams at agreed upon times. The teacher will be happy to explain material during the consultation, but will not teach it again. It is important to request consultations as soon as ambiguities arise so that you can resolve them before exams. You can also view your own tickets in the menu option My tickets to see open and resolved questions.

Your options for consultations are through MS Teams platform, at times agreed with the teacher.
